WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:19.768 --> 01:24.768
Subtitles by explosiveskull

01:26.854 --> 01:28.486
I'm tellin' ya, she
was checkin' me out.

01:28.488 --> 01:30.020
I don't
know where you get

01:30.022 --> 01:31.790
your delusions, laser brain.

01:31.792 --> 01:34.659
It's not a
delusion, it's a fact.

01:34.661 --> 01:37.261
She was checking out
the latest issue of Conan.

01:37.263 --> 01:38.496
Oh, and you're tellin'
me she wasn't looking

01:38.498 --> 01:40.599
right in the general
direction of my butt?

01:40.601 --> 01:44.772
Dude, you were kneeling
right next to the comic.

01:46.739 --> 01:48.606
Okay, maybe she was
looking for Conan,

01:48.608 --> 01:49.841
but she changed her mind

01:49.843 --> 01:51.876
when she saw an
actual male nearby.

01:51.878 --> 01:53.344
Dude, you're a
great guy, but...

01:53.346 --> 01:54.179
No.

01:54.181 --> 01:55.013
No, no, no.

01:55.015 --> 01:56.281
What?

01:56.283 --> 01:58.216
That whole you're a
great guy but thing,

01:58.218 --> 01:59.951
nothing good ever comes
after those words.

01:59.953 --> 02:01.486
Look, what I
was trying to say was...

02:01.488 --> 02:02.787
Like, you're a great guy,

02:02.789 --> 02:04.956
but I like my guys taller.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.123
You're a great guy,

02:06.125 --> 02:07.925
but I think we should
just be friends.

02:07.927 --> 02:09.461
You're a great guy,

02:09.463 --> 02:11.062
but I don't like you looking
through my window at night.

02:11.064 --> 02:11.899
Okay.

02:13.100 --> 02:14.866
Hey, there's Kevin.

02:14.868 --> 02:17.836
The one person we know with
a genuinely happy love life

02:17.838 --> 02:20.771
that's even remotely
reality-based.

02:22.975 --> 02:26.979
Apparently if your reality
is a Tim Burton film.

02:38.124 --> 02:40.859
Life is just a simmering
cauldron of misery,

02:40.861 --> 02:42.493
stirred by heartache,

02:42.495 --> 02:43.763
fueled by pain.

02:47.066 --> 02:48.432
Ah, don't hold it in, dude.

02:48.434 --> 02:49.835
Tell us how you really feel.

02:49.837 --> 02:51.836
What's wrong?

02:51.838 --> 02:53.771
Lemme ask you guys this.

02:53.773 --> 02:55.272
What is the worst possible thing

02:55.274 --> 02:57.475
that somebody can find
out about their girlfriend

02:57.477 --> 03:00.344
that can ruin any hopes
and dreams of the future

03:00.346 --> 03:04.148
and leave their lives
in a smoldering heap?

03:04.150 --> 03:05.884
She was your
secret twin sister

03:05.886 --> 03:07.551
who was separated
from you at birth

03:07.553 --> 03:08.954
when you were both
put into foster care

03:08.956 --> 03:12.525
to hide you from your
evil overlord father.

03:13.594 --> 03:15.326
Remember how
yesterday me and Ashley

03:15.328 --> 03:17.596
went to my cousin's wedding?

03:17.598 --> 03:20.397
Well I ran into my
Great-Aunt Irene.

03:20.399 --> 03:23.668
Turns out to be Ashley's
Great-Aunt Irene also.

03:23.670 --> 03:25.370
- You don't mean?
- Yeah.

03:25.372 --> 03:27.138
We're second cousins.

03:27.140 --> 03:29.976
I had no idea,
Ashley had no idea.

03:31.344 --> 03:34.579
And to think, I was gonna
ask her to marry me.

03:34.581 --> 03:36.114
So what, does that
make, like, holidays

03:36.116 --> 03:37.883
difficult or something?

03:37.885 --> 03:38.719
Really?

03:40.386 --> 03:44.289
Dude, we can't get married
if we're related like that.

03:44.291 --> 03:46.591
Our kids will end up
havin' 11 fingers,

03:46.593 --> 03:47.427
two heads,

03:48.295 --> 03:50.596
or even become a sports fan.

03:51.531 --> 03:53.497
We broke up last night.

03:53.499 --> 03:55.366
Shades of Luke and Leia.

03:55.368 --> 03:57.002
Dude, that sucks.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.537
This is like
when they found out

03:58.539 --> 04:02.542
that Boomer was a bad guy
in Battlestar Galactica.

04:03.910 --> 04:07.646
Well it's not like she
tried to shoot me or anything.

04:07.648 --> 04:09.316
Okay, bad analogy.

04:10.483 --> 04:11.582
Well, hey, listen,
uh, we're goin'

04:11.584 --> 04:12.516
to Spenser's later tonight.

04:12.518 --> 04:13.818
Why don't you come with?

04:13.820 --> 04:15.853
Spenser's, really?

04:15.855 --> 04:18.322
Nobody ever goes to his parties.

04:18.324 --> 04:19.523
Well yeah, but
he's got all those

04:19.524 --> 04:21.158
great Silver Age
comics we can read.

04:21.160 --> 04:23.928
And all the great Silver
Age toys we can play with.

04:23.930 --> 04:26.331
You guys are the best.

04:26.333 --> 04:28.533
We're like you're
Grey Council,

04:28.535 --> 04:31.302
the ruling body of the Minbari.

04:31.304 --> 04:32.771
Just 'cause he has
hair like a Centauri

04:32.773 --> 04:35.072
doesn't mean you can make
a Babylon 5 reference.

04:35.074 --> 04:37.776
I mean, we're more like his
Rebel Alliance or Jedi Order.

04:37.778 --> 04:40.478
Or we could be crew
mates on his ship.

04:40.480 --> 04:43.014
Yeah, leave it to a Trekkie
to make a nautical reference.

04:43.016 --> 04:45.182
You know I'm not
really a Trekkie.

04:45.184 --> 04:46.586
I'm a Brown Coat.

04:48.388 --> 04:49.553
Man, what are you
even doing here anyway?

04:49.555 --> 04:51.889
Shouldn't you be at work?

04:51.891 --> 04:55.393
I'm letting Todd
run things today.

04:55.395 --> 04:56.595
What?

04:56.597 --> 04:59.600
You put Todd in
charge of the store?

05:12.812 --> 05:15.613
Jackpot, here I come, payday.

05:15.615 --> 05:17.247
Here I come.

05:17.249 --> 05:20.317
Hey, uh, can I help
you with something?

05:20.319 --> 05:21.886
I got some comics for sale.

05:21.888 --> 05:23.822
Oh, okay, yeah, happy to help.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.189
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

05:25.191 --> 05:26.925
- Lemme do that.
- Ah, hey, buddy,

05:26.927 --> 05:29.360
I'm a professional at this.

05:29.362 --> 05:31.261
You can be a professional
at handling comics?

05:31.263 --> 05:32.631
Yeah, seriously.

05:32.633 --> 05:34.665
It's a niche field
in Museum Studies.

05:34.667 --> 05:36.768
Actually, a very niche field.

05:36.770 --> 05:40.038
I got my certificate from the
Art Institute of Pittsburgh.

05:40.040 --> 05:42.173
It's in the back if
you wanna see it.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.511
I can go get it if you want.

05:46.312 --> 05:48.646
Okay, I'll trust you.

05:48.648 --> 05:50.615
- Good.
- Good.

05:50.617 --> 05:54.285
- Remember, these are my babies.
- Got ya.

05:54.287 --> 05:55.220
All right.

05:55.222 --> 05:56.620
Your babies, I'll be careful.

05:56.622 --> 05:58.023
- All right?
- Feast your eyes.

05:58.025 --> 06:00.725
See what kind of treasure
you got for me here.

06:00.727 --> 06:03.360
Okay, Death of Superman?

06:03.362 --> 06:06.199
Yeah, mint
condition, number 75.

06:07.566 --> 06:08.565
Okay.

06:08.567 --> 06:11.201
Uh, Death of Superman.

06:11.203 --> 06:13.637
Death of, looks like all
these are Death of Superman.

06:13.639 --> 06:16.141
Well yeah, 50 of 'em!

06:16.143 --> 06:18.576
Camero, here I come.

06:18.578 --> 06:21.346
Slow down
a little bit, buddy.

06:21.348 --> 06:23.113
Um, you wouldn't happen
to have any Beanie Babies

06:23.115 --> 06:25.115
or vacuum-sealed
Cabbage Patch dolls

06:25.117 --> 06:27.351
to help sweeten
the deal, would ya?

06:27.353 --> 06:28.819
You know what, I might!

06:28.821 --> 06:30.288
- Would that really help?
- No, no, no.

06:30.290 --> 06:31.790
'Cause you know my sister
used to collect 'em...

06:31.792 --> 06:32.990
- I was just, just kidding.
- She even had the heads.

06:32.992 --> 06:35.026
Just kidding, back in 1991,

06:35.028 --> 06:37.295
way too many people
horded those things,

06:37.297 --> 06:40.566
way too much supply,
not enough demand.

06:41.802 --> 06:45.069
Well, no, no, no,
no, this is Superman!

06:45.071 --> 06:47.805
Not, not Bird-Man
or Aquaman, Super...

06:47.807 --> 06:51.108
Okay, Superman couldn't even
defeat his greatest enemy.

06:51.110 --> 06:52.310
All right?

06:52.312 --> 06:54.579
I'll give you 20 bucks
for the whole box.

06:54.581 --> 06:57.781
That's the best
you're gonna get.

06:57.783 --> 06:59.350
No, no.

06:59.352 --> 07:00.153
No.

07:00.987 --> 07:02.721
What a crock.

07:02.723 --> 07:04.322
- You know what?
- What?

07:04.324 --> 07:07.492
You run a real
cutthroat operation here.

07:07.494 --> 07:08.526
Yeah, I guess.

07:08.528 --> 07:09.360
Hey!

07:09.362 --> 07:10.196
What?

07:11.364 --> 07:14.264
What if I could get
you a girl to kiss?

07:15.669 --> 07:17.035
Yeah?

07:17.037 --> 07:18.737
- Yeah, little sweeten the deal?
- Nah, not so much.

07:18.739 --> 07:20.939
Uh, you're barkin' up
the wrong tree, buddy.

07:20.941 --> 07:21.775
Sorry.

07:24.410 --> 07:25.244
Fine.

07:26.446 --> 07:29.247
I'm gonna take these to
Mage's on the West Side.

07:29.249 --> 07:30.915
- Not our mortal enemy?
- Yeah, yeah.

07:30.917 --> 07:32.550
- Oh no, please don't!
- Yeah.

07:32.552 --> 07:33.718
Please don't, I tell ya what,

07:33.720 --> 07:36.086
I'll give you 21.09 for those.

07:36.088 --> 07:38.322
Just for that, I'm
takin' my Star Wars

07:38.324 --> 07:41.526
Episode One, Two, and
Three action figures

07:41.528 --> 07:42.694
- and sellin' 'em there.
- No, please don't!

07:42.696 --> 07:44.461
50 cents a piece.

07:44.463 --> 07:46.463
When I get my Camero,

07:46.465 --> 07:48.533
it's gonna look
like the Batmobile.

07:48.535 --> 07:50.300
Yeah, okay, keep dreamin'.

07:50.302 --> 07:51.870
Yeah, a clickety-clunk Camero

07:51.872 --> 07:53.704
from a buy-here-pay-here
lot maybe.

07:53.706 --> 07:54.538
You know what?

07:54.540 --> 07:55.473
Screw you!

07:55.475 --> 07:57.544
Oh whatever, douche bag.

07:58.778 --> 08:00.812
Have fun at Mage's.

08:00.814 --> 08:02.613
God, what a douche bag.

08:02.615 --> 08:05.382
No wonder I sleep on the job.

08:15.227 --> 08:16.728
Hey, Spence, great party.

08:16.730 --> 08:19.163
More than five people
actually showed up.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.004
Hey, guys.

08:27.840 --> 08:29.843
I just don't believe it.

08:31.211 --> 08:33.110
Well this is
sounding familiar.

08:33.111 --> 08:34.211
What's up?

08:34.212 --> 08:36.947
One day, one gorm day

08:36.948 --> 08:38.883
since me and Ashley broke up,

08:38.885 --> 08:40.851
and is she mourning like I am?

08:40.852 --> 08:41.885
Hell no.

08:41.886 --> 08:43.989
She's goin' out on dates.

08:45.091 --> 08:46.557
Well, some people
are different.

08:46.559 --> 08:49.360
Some people like to get
right back up on the horse.

08:49.362 --> 08:52.330
Not only that, she
decides to go out on a date

08:52.332 --> 08:54.932
with that Neanderthal
Chuck Hanaley.

08:54.934 --> 08:56.634
Chuck Hanley.

08:56.636 --> 08:57.568
Isn't he that guy that works

08:57.570 --> 08:58.836
over at Ted's Sporting Goods?

08:58.838 --> 09:01.038
One and the same.

09:01.040 --> 09:03.908
How does she go from a
well-mannered individual,

09:03.910 --> 09:05.275
intelligent,

09:05.277 --> 09:07.144
to somebody that
has to be reminded

09:07.146 --> 09:09.379
to breathe through their nose?

09:09.381 --> 09:11.816
Swear, if he got fresh
with her last night,

09:11.818 --> 09:13.017
I'm gonna walk into that...

09:13.019 --> 09:14.586
All right, hold
on, Captain Reynolds.

09:14.588 --> 09:17.254
Put your brown coat away,
and let's think here.

09:17.256 --> 09:19.456
If we go into Ted's
Sporting Goods half-cocked,

09:19.458 --> 09:20.725
somebody's gonna get hurt,

09:20.727 --> 09:22.192
and it's probably gonna be me.

09:22.194 --> 09:24.762
And I'm not gonna be
Wash this time, damn it.

09:24.764 --> 09:27.631
We have to plan our
moves carefully.

09:27.633 --> 09:29.767
What do you suggest?

09:29.769 --> 09:31.469
We could go over to her work

09:31.471 --> 09:34.105
and ask if Chuck's been
skulking around at all.

09:34.107 --> 09:37.041
Or you could talk to Ashley.

09:37.043 --> 09:38.809
What if Ashley's working?

09:38.811 --> 09:41.479
I don't want her to think
that I'm spyin' on her.

09:41.481 --> 09:43.047
Even though you are.

09:43.049 --> 09:47.051
But I don't
want it to look like I am.

09:47.053 --> 09:48.286
'Kay, tell ya what.

09:48.288 --> 09:50.053
I'll go in first, I'll
scope out the scene,

09:50.055 --> 09:50.989
and, if everything's clear,

09:50.991 --> 09:53.523
I'll ring you on your cell.

09:53.525 --> 09:55.726
You're a good friend.

09:55.728 --> 09:58.230
Okay, just wait for my call.

10:36.670 --> 10:37.902
Hey, Kev?

10:37.904 --> 10:39.673
Coast is clear, dude.

10:41.141 --> 10:42.440
Seriously?

10:42.442 --> 10:44.042
You're gonna call
me from outside

10:44.044 --> 10:46.778
when the shop's right next door.

10:46.780 --> 10:49.047
I said I'd call.

10:49.049 --> 10:49.882
Come on.

11:00.327 --> 11:01.160
Hey, PJ.

11:02.328 --> 11:04.262
Hey, Kevin, what's up?

11:04.264 --> 11:05.596
Not much.

11:05.598 --> 11:07.898
Oh, I know, you
wanna see Ashley.

11:07.900 --> 11:08.899
Hold on, she's in the back room.

11:08.901 --> 11:10.100
Let me go get here.

11:10.102 --> 11:13.272
No, no, no.

11:14.741 --> 11:18.244
And you didn't ask if
she was in the back.

11:19.713 --> 11:21.144
I didn't think of it.

11:21.146 --> 11:22.714
Dude, I swear
if you had brains,

11:22.716 --> 11:24.217
you'd be an idiot.

11:25.218 --> 11:26.819
Hey, Kev.

11:28.755 --> 11:29.655
Hey, Ash.

11:33.593 --> 11:35.259
So how have you been?

11:35.261 --> 11:37.097
Good, how 'bout you?

11:39.098 --> 11:41.231
Uh, you know, I still have that

11:41.233 --> 11:44.469
Hellblazer graphic novel
of yours at the house.

11:44.471 --> 11:49.240
I didn't know if you wanted
me to bring it here or?

11:49.242 --> 11:50.075
No.

11:51.511 --> 11:53.677
Constantine was always
more your thing than mine.

11:53.679 --> 11:55.113
You keep it.

11:55.115 --> 11:57.514
Are you sure.

11:57.516 --> 11:59.583
- Yeah.
- All right.

11:59.585 --> 12:01.219
I guess I'll see ya later.

12:01.221 --> 12:02.054
See ya.

12:31.150 --> 12:32.417
Todd?

12:32.419 --> 12:34.487
You must be Zod Killer?

12:37.223 --> 12:39.389
So, you gotta tell me this.

12:39.391 --> 12:41.958
Your screen name
on dbhookedup.com

12:41.960 --> 12:44.861
is Zod Killer but your
real name is Clark?

12:44.863 --> 12:46.532
Oh, you think I'm.

12:48.001 --> 12:50.735
Todd, there's been something
I've been meaning to tell you.

12:50.737 --> 12:52.072
I am really, no!

12:54.074 --> 12:56.773
I'm just a huge
Superman fan, man.

12:56.775 --> 12:57.908
Yeah, when I found
out that we actually

12:57.910 --> 12:59.744
had the same exact name.

12:59.746 --> 13:02.179
My full name is
Clark Kent Allan.

13:02.181 --> 13:03.480
Well, I was infatuated with him.

13:03.482 --> 13:04.648
I mean, seriously,

13:04.650 --> 13:07.319
I only read Superman
and DC Comics.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.024
Okay, yeah, that's great.

13:14.026 --> 13:15.993
Dude, I can't wait!

13:15.995 --> 13:17.163
Yay.

13:18.131 --> 13:19.996
Oh, Kevin, will you crawl out

13:19.998 --> 13:21.566
of your Ashley-sized hole

13:21.568 --> 13:23.433
long enough to see daylight?

13:23.435 --> 13:26.537
We've been waiting for
this for four years!

13:26.539 --> 13:28.405
I still can't believe it.

13:28.407 --> 13:29.639
Believe it.

13:29.641 --> 13:31.576
Hey, guys, what's up?

13:31.578 --> 13:32.478
Not much.

13:33.913 --> 13:35.513
Yeah, you can say that again.

13:35.515 --> 13:37.715
What's up with Darth
Vasidious over here?

13:37.717 --> 13:40.217
He's mad I won't go
see a movie with him.

13:40.219 --> 13:41.485
A movie?

13:41.487 --> 13:42.753
A movie?

13:42.755 --> 13:44.187
Try the movie

13:44.189 --> 13:45.389
of the century.

13:45.391 --> 13:47.225
Dude, century's only
like 13 years old.

13:47.227 --> 13:48.926
You're gonna have
to be more specific.

13:48.928 --> 13:52.395
It's the movie
adaptation of Hellblazer.

13:52.397 --> 13:54.065
The John Constantine comic?

13:54.067 --> 13:56.333
Didn't they already make one?

13:56.335 --> 14:00.037
Yeah, right, that Keanu
Reeves piece of bantha fodder.

14:00.039 --> 14:02.005
Like that even counts.

14:02.007 --> 14:05.109
Dude, is that, like, a demon?

14:05.111 --> 14:05.944
Bogus.

14:08.615 --> 14:11.749
This is an independent
film from Thailand,

14:11.751 --> 14:13.850
and they didn't get
permission from DC Comics,

14:13.852 --> 14:16.854
so they had to change all
the main characters' names.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.822
A small price to pay.

14:18.824 --> 14:22.960
Finally, a John Constantine
movie that's dark and gritty

14:22.962 --> 14:27.331
and doesn't star some
brain-dead Nic Cage wannabe.

14:27.333 --> 14:29.133
Dude, they changed the
main character's name

14:29.135 --> 14:30.370
to Ben Affleck.

14:32.005 --> 14:33.504
Like that matters.

14:33.506 --> 14:34.538
They could've changed his
name to Brittany Spears

14:34.540 --> 14:36.039
for all I care.

14:36.041 --> 14:37.475
It's just that we,
we've been waiting

14:37.477 --> 14:39.277
to see this for four years,

14:39.279 --> 14:40.477
and now Dave Depression here

14:40.479 --> 14:42.013
is wimping out on going with me.

14:42.015 --> 14:42.848
Look,

14:44.317 --> 14:46.116
Mark's gonna go see a movie,

14:46.118 --> 14:49.019
and I just got the biggest
shipment of the month.

14:49.021 --> 14:52.023
And then Ashley has
a life of her own,

14:52.025 --> 14:54.491
which is more than I
could say for myself.

14:54.493 --> 14:56.159
And I'm stuck here with nobody

14:56.161 --> 14:59.363
to help with the largest
shipment of the month.

14:59.365 --> 15:00.965
Excuse me.

15:00.967 --> 15:02.166
Did I hear you say you
have a new shipment

15:02.168 --> 15:03.400
coming in today?

15:03.402 --> 15:04.735
Yeah, are you
looking for something

15:04.737 --> 15:05.937
that we're out of, or?

15:05.939 --> 15:06.803
Well I was wondering,

15:06.805 --> 15:08.038
do you pull boxes first

15:08.040 --> 15:09.206
or do you catalog
your whole shipment

15:09.208 --> 15:10.640
before itemization?

15:10.642 --> 15:12.143
Do you have enough
boards and bags,

15:12.145 --> 15:15.111
or do those come in
a separate delivery?

15:15.113 --> 15:17.148
Uh, exactly what
are you asking?

15:17.150 --> 15:18.316
Well, I was just noticing

15:18.318 --> 15:20.283
that you can probably
use some help,

15:20.285 --> 15:22.620
and I have some
experience in comic shops.

15:22.622 --> 15:23.955
My name's Carley.

15:23.957 --> 15:25.188
Kevin.

15:25.190 --> 15:27.057
- Where'd you work?
- Comic Underground.

15:27.059 --> 15:28.058
Is that around here?

15:28.060 --> 15:29.493
Uh, no, I just
moved back home.

15:29.495 --> 15:31.361
I've been in Oberlin for
the past couple years.

15:31.363 --> 15:32.964
It's local to there.

15:32.966 --> 15:34.498
