after the movie.

31:45.236 --> 31:48.571
It would've ruined
my Carley time.

31:48.573 --> 31:51.909
You think you can
keep an eye on things?

31:54.413 --> 31:56.779
Now, everybody
take your seats.

31:56.781 --> 32:00.018
And prepare yourselves
for the debut of

32:00.819 --> 32:02.320
Sci-Fi Armageddon.

32:04.423 --> 32:06.623
Here are the decks.

32:06.625 --> 32:10.160
Wait, are these cards that
we build a deck out of, or?

32:10.162 --> 32:11.094
No.

32:11.096 --> 32:12.695
Each box is a well-maintained

32:12.697 --> 32:14.364
and well-balanced playing deck

32:14.366 --> 32:15.464
suited to each player's

32:15.466 --> 32:17.634
individual personalities
and abilities.

32:17.636 --> 32:19.136
A deck this big?

32:20.973 --> 32:23.440
Ash, I'm combining
the mythologies

32:23.442 --> 32:26.242
of eight major and six
minor sci-fi universes

32:26.244 --> 32:27.676
into one game.

32:27.678 --> 32:29.112
There are an unbelievable
amount of scenarios

32:29.114 --> 32:30.814
at play here.

32:30.816 --> 32:33.717
Commander Worf
orders a suicide attack

32:33.719 --> 32:37.554
on the star destroyer
circling Babylon 5.

32:37.556 --> 32:38.922
Expend nine.

32:38.924 --> 32:42.392
Screw God, I've got
my own power cards

32:42.394 --> 32:46.695
