out, watch Dr. Who.

33:07.386 --> 33:08.619
Sounds great.

33:14.626 --> 33:16.092
Ooh, a Stargate.

33:16.094 --> 33:17.861
I get away from the Sith Lords.

33:17.863 --> 33:19.828
Speaking of those
who darken the force,

33:19.830 --> 33:23.333
guess who was in the
store yet again today?

33:23.335 --> 33:24.800
What, was Spenser in again

33:24.802 --> 33:27.903
claiming Jack Kirby
invented Star Wars?

33:27.905 --> 33:30.075
No, it was Chuck Hanley!

33:31.242 --> 33:32.410
Oh dear God.

33:34.279 --> 33:35.979
Anyways, he was in there

33:35.981 --> 33:38.647
tryin' to learn
about geek stuff.

33:38.649 --> 33:39.883
He came in yesterday,

33:39.885 --> 33:43.920
and asked what kind
of stuff Ashley reads.

33:43.922 --> 33:45.989
Somebody shoot me now.

33:45.991 --> 33:47.790
What'd you tell him?

33:47.792 --> 33:49.826
I tried to throw him off,

33:49.828 --> 33:53.730
- uh, telling him...
- Spit it out, elf girl.

33:53.732 --> 33:56.932
Telling him you read
a lot of lesbian erotica

33:56.934 --> 33:58.169
graphic novels.

33:59.870 --> 34:01.070
And?

34:01.072 --> 34:03.073
- And he bought six books.
- Ew!

34:03.075 --> 34:05.808
Seemed really
excited about it, too.

34:05.810 --> 34:07.242
Ew.

34:07.244 --> 34:10.212
I'm putting down a
brigade of space marines.

34:10.214 --> 34:11.480
Great.

34:11.482 --> 34:12.748
That saves you from
both my sarlacc pit

34:12.751 --> 34:14.949
and Kevin's Cylon Basestar.

34:14.952 --> 34:16.185
Seriously, Mark?

34:16.187 --> 34:18.920
You used the 1970s
Cylon Baseship?

34:18.922 --> 34:20.489
Well I didn't have a choice.

34:20.492 --> 34:22.091
That newer series
was an abomination

34:22.092 --> 34:24.194
against the gods of sci-fi.

34:24.196 --> 34:25.594
I know, heaven
forbid we add depth

34:25.597 --> 34:27.464
or shading to our characters.

34:27.466 --> 34:30.632
Yeah, and it becomes
I Was a Teenage Cylon.

34:30.635 --> 34:31.734
The only thing
worthwhile on that show

34:31.735 --> 34:33.601
was Katee Sackhoff.

34:33.603 --> 34:35.773
My kinda woman.

34:38.443 --> 34:41.009
Kaylee Frye, uh, from Firefly.

34:41.011 --> 34:44.480
I just discovered I had
a Kaylee in my deck.

34:44.482 --> 34:45.813
Wow, Mark, I'm
surprised you're using

34:45.815 --> 34:48.884
such a new series as
Firefly in your deck.

34:48.886 --> 34:49.821
Well, in,

34:51.089 --> 34:53.455
in this era of
cross-platforming,

34:53.456 --> 34:54.556
we have to appeal

34:54.559 --> 34:57.192
- to such a wide fan base.
- I made him.

34:57.194 --> 34:58.028
Really?

34:59.231 --> 35:00.863
Yeah, I've been,
uh, alpha testing

35:00.865 --> 35:02.799
this monstrosity with him.

35:02.801 --> 35:05.200
Told him if he didn't
pander to the Brown Coats,

35:05.202 --> 35:06.201
I'd leave him to test things

35:06.203 --> 35:07.404
with this Vietnamese kid

35:07.406 --> 35:09.538
who stalks him on Twitter.

35:09.540 --> 35:11.975
And she dumps this
on me last week.

35:11.977 --> 35:15.912
So I need to integrate
60 new cards in six days.

35:15.914 --> 35:18.680
And when did you
spring this on him?

35:18.682 --> 35:19.915
Last week,

35:19.917 --> 35:23.153
after you said how
much you like Firefly.

35:23.155 --> 35:24.990
Aw, that's so sweet.

36:24.281 --> 36:26.616
- Hey.
- Hey, Clark.

36:26.618 --> 36:29.084
I've been doing a lot of
soul-searching lately,

36:29.086 --> 36:32.354
and I really thought I
found the perfect guy,

36:32.356 --> 36:34.122
but I keep asking myself,

36:34.124 --> 36:35.124
can I really be with someone

36:35.126 --> 36:37.894
that only reads DC Comics?

36:37.896 --> 36:40.029
I looked deep into my heart,

36:40.031 --> 36:41.830
and I've come to a conclusion,

36:41.832 --> 36:44.668
and the answer is
no, not so much.

36:59.251 --> 37:02.084
I wish I could've
been there for that.

37:02.086 --> 37:04.053
You know, I think
Kevin's developing

37:04.055 --> 37:05.787
a little crush on you.

37:05.789 --> 37:08.658
- Oh, you noticed that, too.
- Mm hmm.

37:08.660 --> 37:10.759
Yeah, I wonder if I can
just let him down easily,

37:10.761 --> 37:12.294
or if I just ignore
his advances,

37:12.296 --> 37:13.962
maybe he'll go away.

37:13.964 --> 37:15.832
This is Kevin
we're talking about.

37:15.834 --> 37:18.801
Remember the dog through
the window incident?

37:18.803 --> 37:19.971
Ay, caramba.

37:21.138 --> 37:23.138
So what are you doin'
two nights from tonight?

37:23.140 --> 37:24.607
Nothing.

37:24.609 --> 37:26.575
I'm officially bumming
for company all week, why?

37:26.577 --> 37:29.011
You wanna
come over for some D&D?

37:29.013 --> 37:31.314
Dungeons and Dragons?

37:31.316 --> 37:32.149
Sure.

37:33.551 --> 37:36.586
I don't know, I'm not
very good around new people.

37:36.588 --> 37:38.087
Oh, don't worry.

37:38.089 --> 37:39.721
These are some of my best
friends in the whole world,

37:39.723 --> 37:43.160
and I promise you will
have a great time.

37:44.595 --> 37:47.830
If it means that
much to you, then okay.

37:47.832 --> 37:48.932
Good.

37:48.934 --> 37:51.301
And it's a pressure-free
platonic date.

37:51.303 --> 37:52.868
But this means I get to choose

37:52.870 --> 37:55.004
what's on the agenda
tomorrow night.

37:55.006 --> 37:56.171
Tomorrow night?

37:56.173 --> 37:57.674
We're hanging out
tomorrow night as well?

37:57.676 --> 37:59.676
- Are you doin' anything?
- No, but...

37:59.678 --> 38:00.910
But nothing.

38:00.912 --> 38:02.879
You're coming over to
Kevin's for movie night.

38:02.881 --> 38:04.013
Movie night?

38:04.015 --> 38:05.314
Two times a month,

38:05.316 --> 38:07.383
Kevin, Todd, Mark,
Ashley, and myself

38:07.385 --> 38:11.453
get together, watch new
and or classic films.

38:11.455 --> 38:12.921
It's my turn to choose the film,

38:12.923 --> 38:16.694
and I found this really
awesome indie romcom.

38:18.028 --> 38:19.194
Well are you sure
they don't mind

38:19.196 --> 38:21.397
bringing somebody
without checking first?

38:21.399 --> 38:23.366
I don't wanna impose myself.

38:23.368 --> 38:24.700
Whatever, you're awesome.

38:24.702 --> 38:27.569
No one can complain
about my bringing you.

38:27.571 --> 38:30.406
Mm, well then it's
two platonic dates.

38:30.408 --> 38:31.607
If we keep this up,

38:31.609 --> 38:33.542
we'll need to petition Webster's

38:33.544 --> 38:35.812
to expand the
definition of platonic

38:35.814 --> 38:38.113
to include platonically
going steady.

38:38.115 --> 38:39.048
Are you kidding?

38:39.050 --> 38:40.950
I'm a regular platonic Don Juan.

38:44.356 --> 38:47.624
Okay,
guys, so what's first?

38:47.626 --> 38:48.725
I was thinkin'
we could either go

38:48.727 --> 38:50.828
classic sci-fi or Marvel.

38:51.930 --> 38:54.997
Uh, Star Wars, original
trilogy of course.

38:54.999 --> 38:57.466
Close Encounters, Saturn 13.

38:57.468 --> 39:01.238
Iron Man, Iron Man 2,
Thor, Captain America.

39:02.374 --> 39:06.011
How about a movie
we've never seen before?

39:08.078 --> 39:10.513
You know, like, a new movie?

39:10.515 --> 39:13.182
You don't watch new
movies with your friends.

39:13.184 --> 39:15.017
Seriously, never?

39:15.019 --> 39:16.618
New movies are a dicey thing.

39:16.620 --> 39:18.354
I mean, you're
either gonna like 'em

39:18.356 --> 39:19.555
or you're gonna spend
the whole evening

39:19.557 --> 39:20.823
writhing in agony,

39:20.825 --> 39:23.792
hoping for it to be over with.

39:23.794 --> 39:25.261
Yeah, you know.

39:25.263 --> 39:27.562
Like, you like the movie, but
your friend could hate it.

39:27.564 --> 39:28.765
And then you just
spent your whole night

39:28.767 --> 39:30.966
arguing about who's right.

39:30.968 --> 39:32.669
I mean, either way,

39:32.671 --> 39:35.571
it's an uncomfortable
place to be in.

39:35.573 --> 39:37.839
But, Kevin, we
always used to watch

39:37.841 --> 39:39.875
new movies together.

39:39.877 --> 39:42.377
Yeah, no we didn't.

39:42.379 --> 39:44.247
What are you talking about?

39:44.249 --> 39:47.116
We used to watch new movies
together all the time.

39:47.118 --> 39:49.185
We would pick out what we
wanted the night before,

39:49.187 --> 39:50.886
and then I would pick
it up and bring it over

39:50.888 --> 39:52.522
on my way to your house.

39:52.524 --> 39:55.058
Yeah, but I'd download
it the night before,

39:55.060 --> 39:56.325
'cause, you know, I like

39:56.327 --> 39:57.560
watchin' my movies
straight through,

39:57.562 --> 39:59.828
and half the time,
we'd be makin' out.

39:59.830 --> 40:01.830
So you pre-watched the movie

40:01.832 --> 40:04.500
so you wouldn't miss
anything by kissing me?

40:04.502 --> 40:06.334
Hey, I didn't
do it just for me.

40:06.336 --> 40:08.303
I did it for you, too.

40:08.305 --> 40:09.805
Oh really?

40:09.807 --> 40:11.540
Yeah, I'd time it out.

40:11.542 --> 40:12.941
That way, when we
were making out

40:12.943 --> 40:14.576
during the bad times,

40:14.578 --> 40:15.511
and through the
rest of the time,

40:15.513 --> 40:18.714
we'd just be watchin' the movie.

40:18.716 --> 40:20.816
Well, we did have a ton of sex

40:20.818 --> 40:22.653
during the sex scenes.

40:23.888 --> 40:25.520
Yeah, we did.

40:25.522 --> 40:27.557
Dude, the average
sex scene in a movie

40:27.559 --> 40:29.991
is under 120 seconds.

40:29.993 --> 40:33.296
Hey, I found the
pause button, okay?

40:33.298 --> 40:36.866
At least you could
find that button.

40:36.868 --> 40:38.636
Boom, in your face.

40:48.713 --> 40:50.712
Guys, this is so weird.

40:50.714 --> 40:52.214
So I went on a date
for the first time

40:52.216 --> 40:53.783
since the breakup
last night, right?

40:53.785 --> 40:55.417
Yay!

40:55.419 --> 40:56.685
I don't know.

40:56.687 --> 40:57.720
We really didn't connect
or anything like that.

40:57.722 --> 40:58.955
Oh.

40:58.957 --> 41:00.223
But guess what?

41:00.225 --> 41:01.691
People are comin' up to me,

41:01.693 --> 41:04.794
makin' comments to me
about my date last night.

41:04.796 --> 41:07.229
Things that they
shouldn't even know about.

41:07.231 --> 41:08.830
Like, Spenser came up to me

41:08.832 --> 41:10.098
and asked me how the movie was

41:10.100 --> 41:12.200
that me and her went to.

41:12.202 --> 41:14.035
I didn't tell anybody
about what I did last night

41:14.037 --> 41:15.772
until just now.

41:15.774 --> 41:17.707
And then I have Miss
Giggle Fits over here

41:17.709 --> 41:19.241
makin' comments about
me takin' my date

41:19.243 --> 41:20.609
to dinner at Denny's.

41:20.611 --> 41:21.743
Well, gee, you really know how

41:21.745 --> 41:23.845
to spoil a girl, don't you?

41:23.847 --> 41:27.049
Anyways, how'd
she know about that?

41:27.051 --> 41:28.917
Maybe because guys
have no imagination

41:28.919 --> 41:31.187
